tury Vampire Hunter Idea. </span><hr size=1> When I say Vampire, I mean anything that can't be killed with a convential bullet and knife and requires intimate knowledge and lore of its kind. <br>
In short, his name is Phillipe Chasseur. He's French (as if the name didn't give it away) He belongs to a centuries old elite order of Witch Hunters. Governed by a council of 13. <br>
I'm trying to decide some specifics and background that would make him an interesting character with deep, deep motives, Like Alucard (the character, not the mod) but something further down the family line or something.<br>
Any ideas?<br>
Also, one more thing, a big huge FF Style sword, or a stylised Rapier? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ulordgabriel3.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lord Gabriel 3</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/14/02 1:47:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=497.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/dogfuchow/pie.jpg height=120 width=120></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 17th Century Vampire Hunter Idea. </span><hr size=1> About the swords, a hilted broadsword is more likely, since a rapier can't do much exponential damage. The enormous FF swords are ridiculous, but okay.<br>
<br>
As far as motivation, I'm stumped. <p><b>Gaealord Gabriel Angelo Maokai III</b>
<br>
"<i>What's little, red and getting smaller? A baby playing with a potato peeler. What's the difference between a truckfull of babies and a truckfull of bowling balls? You can't pick up bowling balls with a pitchfork. What's worse than a pile of dead babies? The one at the bottom trying to eat his way out.</i>" LG3, <i>Kizoku no Idiots</i><br><a href ="http://pub66.ezboard.com/bkizokunoidiots"><img src="http://members.aol.com/dogfuchow/banner1.jpg"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ubutterflyparadox.showPublicProfile?language=EN>butterflyparadox</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://liquid2k.com/blueparadox/moon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/14/02 9:11:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=497.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://liquid2k.com/blueparadox/red.jpg width=100 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 17th Century Vampire Hunter Idea. </span><hr size=1> I like his last name 'hunter'......and you could develope your idea more by thinking about the exact kind of vampire he is....eg...the typical kind that sires other vampires with one bite? or does it require some kind of ritual to change people into vampires? and if so....does he make other vampires? and if not, why not? what are his reasons? it's good how you have chosen the number 13 for the council....does this council have rules that have to be followed, is it a good council? or is it corrupted?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  okay, maybe that was too heavy, they were questions that popped into my mind as I read your description, anyhoo sounds like a very interesting idea <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ujefm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jefm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/14/02 10:12:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=497.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 17th Century Vampire Hunter Idea. </span><hr size=1> Big swords like FF and claymore type or any big double bladed two handed sword is not for elegant combat...it's for crushing bones and maybe dismemberment...they are cumbersome heavy and meant for battling many enemies with lots of armour....because they can be swung with some momentum and penetrate the armour or at least knock a couple enemies on their butts...<br>
for elegant sword play single bladed light swords are best especially curved ones like rapiers (they're curved arent they?) and katana's...the curve makes the point of contact smaller making it easier to simply cut an enemy in half effortlessly...and easier to draw...<br>
I'm not a sword expert so I could be off...but someone will probably point out my mistakes <p><pre>
