</pre></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ulordgabriel3.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lord Gabriel 3</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/15/02 12:20:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=497.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/dogfuchow/pie.jpg height=120 width=120></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 17th Century Vampire Hunter Idea. </span><hr size=1> a rapier is a thin thrusting sword; it can't pierce through heavy clothing, and really doesn't do that much physical damage, especially when you're talking about killing the immortal undead. A rapier is best used when stabbing through vital organs, but they're useless against vampires (other than perhaps silver). I'd say that a butchering sword that isn't made for heavy armor would probably do the trick. Thus, a broadsword is heavy enough to chop off limbs, but isn't for armor. Another suggestion, the longsword is for a tall, limber hunter (Vampie Hunter D, for instance) and is a very lightweight weapon in comparison to the broadsword, but may be too long to handle. A katana would be a good weapon, but I don't think it's likely a Frenchman would use one. Quartermoon blades like a katana can sometimes be customized though, like in Blade, so that's probably the best bet. And don't forget the silver. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><b>Gaealord Gabriel Angelo Maokai III</b>
