"<i>What's little, red and getting smaller? A baby playing with a potato peeler. What's the difference between a truckfull of babies and a truckfull of bowling balls? You can't pick up bowling balls with a pitchfork. What's worse than a pile of dead babies? The one at the bottom trying to eat his way out.</i>" LG3, <i>Kizoku no Idiots</i><br><a href ="http://pub66.ezboard.com/bkizokunoidiots"><img src="http://members.aol.com/dogfuchow/banner1.jpg"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ubritboyj.showPublicProfile?language=EN>britboyJ</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/15/02 6:52:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=497.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> SUBJECT</span><hr size=1> What about a cutlass?<br>
As for teh vampire idea, I was going to say that he wasn't necissarily a vampire, but that someone down his family line, he has something he feels cursed by and the subsequent generations have tried too. <br>
The council of 13 is originally good. They govern the witch hunters (lots of them back then) and the Vampire hunters. They do however, at some point in the story, all become vampires. <br>
I was thinking of using the kind of Vampire &quot;Blood Lines&quot; like in Warhammer, The Von Carsteins are the &quot;standard&quot; Dracula-esque vampires. (&quot;Aristocracy of the Night&quot;) <br>
And there's Lahmia vampires, deadly women who seduce then suck the blood of thier &quot;patrons&quot; <br>
There's the Necharchs. Necromancers who's only chance to live is through a blood lust they shoved on themselves to live longer.<br>
And the Blood Dragons. Knights who's whole order is cursed with vampirism, but they all desperately want to be rid of it, so they try and find thier master, who drank teh blood of a dragon and was cured. <br>
As for the giant Strigoi, I have no clue, not got 6th Edition. Anyone?<br>
Of course i'd change these up, I just don't like having Dracula clones and buffy-esque vampires everywhere. <br>
And don't forget Werewolves and other nasty htings that go bump in the night. <br>
BTW, how do you kill a Succubus? (If indeed, you can kill one)<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/upuerumbris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Puer Umbris </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.liquid2k.com/oolong/005.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/16/02 9:10:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=497.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/oolong/005.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SUBJECT</span><hr size=1> He could use a sabre!  It is as quick as a rapier, but can do much more damage.  Also, he might be able to use an eppe.  For those of you who arent into fencing, and eppe is a heavy rapier that has a bit of a sharper edge.  It would be great for hacking down the hordes of skeletons! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=windblade>windblade</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/17/02 4:42:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=497.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SUBJECT</span><hr size=1> hmmmm... since we're talking weapons, how'bout a falchion? <br>
